for segmentation btw

Good — segmentation changes the format slightly, but the idea is the same.

For YOLO segmentation (YOLO26-seg / Ultralytics seg models) you are no longer storing just boxes — you store masks (polygons).

1. Dataset structure (segmentation)

Same as detection:

dataset/
├── images/
│   ├── train/
│   └── val/
├── labels/
│   ├── train/
│   └── val/
└── data.yaml
2. Label format (THIS is the key difference)

Instead of bounding boxes, each object is:

class_id x1 y1 x2 y2 x3 y3 ...

These are polygon points normalized (0–1).

Example:
0 0.10 0.20 0.15 0.25 0.20 0.22 0.18 0.18

That represents:

class 0
a polygon around the object

Each line = one object.

3. What YOLO segmentation is doing

Internally:

it converts polygons → masks
trains a mask head (not just box head)
outputs both:
bounding box
segmentation mask

So your model becomes:

